quran[29]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,154,"What is it with you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>? How do you judge?"
  37,155,"Will you not <span class=""h"">remind<sup foot_note=""80986"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">yourselves</span>?"
  37,156,"Or do you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>have an evident manifestation?"
  37,157,"Then bring your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>scripture, if you have been truthful."
  37,158,"And they invented a relationship between Him and<i class=""s"">(the race of) </i>unseen beings{1}. And certainly,<i class=""s"">(the race of) </i>unseen beings knew that they<i class=""s"">(who made the claims) </i>would surely be arraigned—",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is jinnahwhich is the race of unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.
  37,159,"Highly Exalted is Allah far above what they describe—"
  37,160,"except for Allah’s <span class=""h"">sincere chosen<sup foot_note=""80988"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>servants."
  37,161,"Thus surely, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>and what you worship"
  37,162,"can never seduce<i class=""s"">(anyone) </i>away from Him,"
  37,163,"except for one who is to roast in purgatory."
  37,164,"“And there is not one of us{1}but has an assigned position.",footnotes:1:The angels.
  37,165,"And we are indeed the aligned."
  37,166,"And we are indeed those who exalt God.”"
  37,167,"Even though they{1}used to say,",footnotes:1:The disbelievers.
  37,168,"“Had we received a Reminder from the ancients{1},",footnotes:1:Ponder this with Verse 38:1.
  37,169,"we would have been Allah’s sincere chosen servants.”"
  37,170,"But they denied it, so they will find out."
  37,171,"And most surely Our Word has already gone out to our servant emissaries:"
  37,172,"indeed, it is they who shall surely be supported,"
  37,173,"and indeed it is Our soldiers who shall surely be the overcomers."
  37,174,"So turn<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>away from them for some time,"
  37,175,"and watch them—for they will soon see."
  37,176,"Do they seek to hasten Our punishment?"
  37,177,"Yet, when it descends into their courtyard, miserable shall be the morning of those forewarned{1}.",footnotes:1:Ponder this with 38:11.
  37,178,"And turn<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>away from them for a while,"
  37,179,"and watch—they will soon see."
  37,180,"Highly Exalted is your Lord, the Lord of Might, far above what they describe."
  37,181,"And peace be upon the emissaries."
  37,182,"And all praise be to Allah, Lord of all realms."
